*Urgently required Capacity Building Expert (Female)*

*PriMove Infrastructure Development Consultants Pvt. Ltd.*

*Location:* Pune (Maharashtra)

*Position:* Capacity Building Expert (Female)

*About PriMove*

We, PriMove Infrastructure Development Consultants Pvt. Ltd, are a leading service provider in the field of various engineering services and capacity building services since 1999. The organization has been promoted and managed by professionals to provide support services to the Government, Multilateral and bilateral agencies, NGOs, Corporate, Urban Local Bodies (Municipal Governments), and Rural Local Bodies (Zilla Panchayats).

PriMove provides various services in the field of Water Supply, Sewage, Storm Water Management, Highways & Bridges, Rural & Urban Sanitation, Environmental Planning, Water Resource Development, Natural Resource Management, Renewable energy & Agriculture.

The spectrum of our services ranges widely from robust Engineering Designs, Topographical Surveys, Aerial Surveys, Feasibility Studies, Preparation of DPR, Preparation of Master plans, Project Management Consultancy, preparation of development plans, Capacity Building, Training & Institution Development, Policy Research, and Documentation.

We have also developed technologies in the sector of rural sanitation, sewerage treatment, and water purification. We are also acting as a support as well as an implementing organization, for various initiatives in the field of Corporate Social Responsibility delivering end-to-end solutions. We are a learning organization with an open work culture. We promote teamwork and a professional working environment with a strong value system.

*Required Qualification:*

• Post Graduate (PG) degree in Social Science / Sociology or a closely related field

*Required Experience:*

• At least 7 years of experience in conducting TNA / CAN, facilitating of trainings and workshops, design of modules and manual in the field of Livelihood / Agriculture / Agri Business / Entrepreneurship Development of SHGs / FPOs / Farmers. 

*Job Description:*

1. Assist team for carrying out inception activities and preparing inception report along with work plan
2. Contribute to the development of Capacity Needs Assessment (CNA) framework and study tools.
3. Build capacity of in-house team for undertaking CNA work and prepare field work plan
4. Prepare CNA report in consultation with team covering comprehensive Capacity Building (CB) plans that address identified capacity gaps and priorities
5. Assist team to finalize MTs selection criteria 
6. Prepare training module and manuals
7. Training facilitation – 6 ToTs and 12 Trainings 
8. Provide handholding support to seller / MTs for on-boarding, undertaking transactions, 
9. Prepare framework for mapping training impact and build the capacity of internal staff, MTs for conducing impact assessment work.
10. Provide on-going support and mentorship to master trainers to enhance their training delivery capabilities.
11. Provide guidance and support to project teams on implementing monitoring protocols and capturing relevant data.
12. Plan and conduct training output studies to assess the impact and outcomes of capacity-building interventions and develop note
13. Prepare template for case studies documentation and undertake follow up for its compilation.
14. Extend support to team for preparing progress reports timely by sharing key activities under CB components, training monitoring etc.
15. Assist team for preparing final report consisting, outputs, outcomes, and lessons learned into a final report.
